@startuml pr-model-file-cases-all
title PR Cases for a model file (per-path flow)

start

note right
  Terminology (see doc/README.md):
  - source = PR head ref
  - target = PR base ref
  - merge base = common ancestor commit
end note

:Is path relevant (matches configured model extension)?;
if (Relevant?) then (yes)
  :Determine file status (added/deleted/modified/renamed);

  if (Added or deleted?) then (yes)
    :Report outcome: creation/deletion at file level;
  else (no)
    :Resolve metamodel for this file;
    if (Metamodel resolved?) then (yes)
      :Load source and target versions as models;
      if (Both versions load?) then (yes)
        if (Both conform to resolved metamodel?) then (yes)
          :Compute merge base and decide comparison mode;
          if (Both source and target changed vs merge base?) then (yes)
            :Case: 3-way comparison → <3-way-comparison.puml>;
          else (no)
            :Case: 2-way comparison → <2-way-comparison.puml>;
          endif
        else (no)
          :Case: metamodel conformance failure;
          :Report outcome: analysis incomplete or invalid model;
        endif
      else (no)
        :Case: parse/load failure;
        :Report outcome: analysis incomplete;
      endif
    else (no)
      :Case: metamodel resolution failure;
      :Report outcome: analysis incomplete;
    endif
  endif

else (no)
  :Skip: not a configured model file;
endif

:Report posted/updated as PR comment;

stop
@enduml
